HEADWORD: Uniformism
<hw>U"ni*form`ism</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From
<er>Uniform</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Geol.)</fld> <def>The doctrine of
uniformity in the geological history of the earth; -- in part equivalent
to <xex>uniformitarianism</xex>, but also used, more broadly, as opposed
to <xex>catastrophism</xex>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Uniformitarian</ent>⟦br⟧
